data.text:
From my hometown, Barrow in Furness...

The late Emlyn Hughes - Footballer

Michael Absalom - Television presenter.

Steve Dixon - Newsreader for Sky News.

Nigel Kneale - Film and television scriptwriter.

Dave Myers - (Hairy) Biker turned TV Chef.

Karen Taylor - TV Comedienne.

Dame Stella Rimington - Former Director-General (DG) of MI5.

Nella Last. Wartime diarist and subject of Victoria Wood's Housewife, 49

More people listed here...

http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_residents_of_Barrow-in-Furness

Oh, and Stan Laurel was born about nine miles up the road in Ulverston.

0

I live just outside Newcastle, Tim Healy was from here... but in Newcastle their is.....

Cardinal Basil Hume, Archbishop of Westminster (1976-1999) was born in the city in 1923. A statue of the Cardinal (unveiled by the Queen in 2002) stands outside St Mary's Cathedral in a memorial garden dedicated to the religious leader. Other notable people born in or associated with Newcastle include: Engineer and industrialist Lord Armstrong, Engineer Robert Stephenson, rock star Sting, Lord Taylor, Miriam Stoppard, comedian Rowan Atkinson (from Stocksfield in northumberland), entertainers Ant and Dec, and international footballers Peter Beardsley and Alan Shearer.

0

Born in Northampton. Des O'Connor and Robert Llewellyn are from there, and Robert Llewellyn lived near my friend until fairly recently.

The soap opera actress (I think) and ex-member of kiddie-pop group All*Stars, Rebecca Hunter, is also from there and was in one of my classes at college. Her real name is Becky Jones and I think she's married to Dom of Da Bungalow fame now.
